DevSecOps Associate
1-2

We are looking for a smart and enthusiastic fresher who wants to start a career in DevSecOps. This role combines development, security, and operations. You will learn how modern software teams build, secure and deliver applications.

Key Responsibilities
Support senior team members in running and maintaining CI/CD pipelines (automated build and deployment systems).
Learn how to use different security tools that check code quality and vulnerabilities.
Assist in simple automation tasks using scripting languages (Python/Shell/YAML).
Help in basic cloud activities on platforms like AWS, Azure, or GCP.
Work with tools that scan applications, containers (Docker), and system security.
Document processes, update task trackers, and follow standard workflows.
Participate in team discussions, training sessions, and improvement activities.

What We Are Looking For
Basic understanding of programming or scripting.
Comfortable working on Linux and using Git/GitHub.
Interest in DevOps, cybersecurity, automation, or cloud technologies.
Good communication skills and ability to ask questions when needed.
Strong willingness to learn new tools and technologies.

Nice to Have (Optional)
Any internship or academic project in cloud, DevOps, or security.
Basic idea of Docker or Kubernetes.
Certifications (even beginner-level) in Cloud/DevOps/Security.

Who You Are
Curious and eager to learn.
Detail-oriented and responsible.
Enjoys teamwork and problem solving.
Open to guidance and feedback from seniors.

Education
BE/BTech/BSc/MCA in Computer Science, IT, or related fields.

Why Join Us
Opportunity to learn directly from experienced DevSecOps professionals.
Exposure to modern tools and technologies used in real projects.
Supportive environment with structured training sessions.
Strong career growth in DevOps, Cloud, and Security domains.
